59// The number of samples to extract for arithmetic intensity curves
60static const int ARITH_INTENSITY_CURVE_SAMPLE_N = 10;
61
62// Annotation position encoding
63enum class AnnotationPosType : int {
64 kPosNone = 0, // Does not have this kind of annotation
65 kPosInnerSpatial = 1, // The annotated iterator is the innermost spatial iterator
66 kPosMiddleSpatial = 2, // The annotated iterator is a middle spatial iterator
67 kPosOuterSpatial = 3, // The annotated iterator is the outermost spatial iterator
68 kPosInnerReduce = 4, // The annotated iterator is the innermost reduce iterator
69 kPosMiddleReduce = 5, // The annotated iterator is a middle reduce iterator
70 kPosOuterReduce = 6, // The annotated iterator is the outermost reduce iterator
71 kPosMixed = 7 // The annotated iterator is a mixed space and reduce iterator
72};
73
74// Buffer access type
75enum class BufferAccessType : int { kRead = 0, kWrite = 1, kReadWrite = 2, kUnknownRW = 3 };
76
77// Accesses to a buffer
78struct BufferAccess {
79 // data reuse type
80 BufferAccessType acc_type{BufferAccessType::kUnknownRW};
81 // Use a two-dimensional array to store multiple multi-dimensional accesses.
82 // The innermost vector stores the multi-dimensional indices of one access.
83 std::vector<std::vector<PrimExpr>> indices;
84};
85
86// Data reuse type
87enum class ReuseType : int { kLoopMultipleRead = 0, kSerialMultipleReadWrite = 1, kNoReuse = 2 };
88
89// Feature for an access of a buffer
90struct BufferAccessFeature {
91 std::string buffer_name; // The name of the buffer
92 BufferAccessType acc_type; // The type of the access
93 float bytes; // The touched memory in bytes
94 float unique_bytes; // The touched unique memory in bytes
95 float lines; // The number of touched cache lines
96 float unique_lines; // The number touched unique cache lines
97 ReuseType reuse_type; // Tye type of data reuse
98 float reuse_dis_iter; // The reuse distance in iterator number
99 float reuse_dis_bytes; // The reuse distance in total touched bytes
100 float reuse_ct; // The reuse ratio
101 float bytes_d_reuse_ct; // bytes / reuse_ct
102 float unique_bytes_d_reuse_ct; // unique_bytes / reuse_ct
103 float lines_d_reuse_ct; // lines / reuse_ct
104 float unique_lines_d_reuse_ct; // unique_lines / reuse_ct
105 float stride; // The stride in access
106};

108// Feature set of a BufferStore statement
109struct FeatureSet {
110 // Group 1: Computation related features
111 float float_mad; // The number of float MAD (Multiply–add) ops
112 float float_addsub; // The number of float add and sub ops
113 float float_mul; // The number of float multiply ops
114 float float_divmod; // The number of float div and mod ops
115 float float_cmp; // The number of float comparison ops
116 float float_math_func; // The number of float math func calls
117 float float_other_func; // The number of other float func calls
118 float int_mad; // The number of integer MAD (Multiply–add) ops
119 float int_addsub; // The number of integer add and sub ops
120 float int_mul; // The number of float multiply ops
121 float int_divmod; // The number of float div and mod ops
122 float int_cmp; // The number of float comparison ops
123 float int_math_func; // The number of float math func calls
124 float int_other_func; // The number of other float func calls
125 float bool_op; // The number of bool ops
126 float select_op; // The number of select ops
127 float vec_num; // The number of vectorized iterators
128 float vec_prod; // The product of the lengths of vectorized iterators
129 float vec_len; // The length of the innermost vectorized iterator
130 AnnotationPosType vec_type; // The type of vectorization position
131 float unroll_num; // The number of unrolled iterators
132 float unroll_prod; // The product of the lengths of vectorized iterators
133 float unroll_len; // The length of the innermost unrolled iterator
134 AnnotationPosType unroll_type; // The type of unroll position
135 float parallel_num; // The number of paralleled iterators
136 float parallel_prod; // The product of the lengths of paralleled iterators
137 float parallel_len; // The length of the innermost paralleled iterators
138 AnnotationPosType parallel_type; // The type of parallel position
139 float is_gpu; // Whether it is a GPU task
140 float blockIdx_x_len; // The length of blockIdx.x
141 float blockIdx_y_len; // The length of blockIdx.y
142 float blockIdx_z_len; // The length of blockIdx.z
143 float threadIdx_x_len; // The length of threadIdx.x
144 float threadIdx_y_len; // The length of threadIdx.y
145 float threadIdx_z_len; // The length of threadIdx.z
146 float vthread_len; // The length of virtual thread
147
148 // Group 2: Buffer access related features (per buffer)
149 std::vector<BufferAccessFeature> access_feas;
150
151 // Group 3: Arithmetic intensity related features
152 float arith_intensity_curve[ARITH_INTENSITY_CURVE_SAMPLE_N]; // points sampled from the
153 // arithmetic intensity curve
154
155 // Group 4: Allocation related features
156 float alloc_size; // The size of allocated buffer in bytes
157 float alloc_outer_prod; // The product of lengths of loops outside the scope of the allocation
158 float alloc_inner_prod; // The product of lengths of loops inside the score of the allocation
159 float alloc_prod; // alloc_outer_prod * alloc_inner_prod
160
161 // Group 5: Outer scope related features
162 float outer_prod; // The product of lengths of outer loops
163 float num_loops; // The number of outer loops
164 float auto_unroll_max_step; // The value of pragma "auto_unroll_max_step"
165};

167// Return whether a var is in an expr
168bool VarInExpr(const Var& var, const PrimExpr& expr) {
169 bool find = false;
170
171 PostOrderVisit(expr, [&find, &var](const ObjectRef& node) {
172 if (find) {
173 return;
174 }
175
176 if (const VarNode* op = node.as<VarNode>()) {
177 if (op == var.get()) {
178 find = true;
179 }
180 }
181 });
182
183 return find;
184}
185
186// Get position encoding for annotation
187AnnotationPosType GetAnnotationPosEncoding(const Var& var, const Array<PrimExpr>& spatial_args,
188 const Array<IterVar>& axis,
189 const Array<IterVar>& reduce_axis) {
190 // Try to match spatial args first
191 size_t find_i = 0;
192 size_t find_ct = 0;
193 for (size_t i = 0; i < spatial_args.size(); ++i) {
194 if (VarInExpr(var, spatial_args[i])) {
195 find_i = i;
196 find_ct += 1;
197 }
198 }
199
200 if (find_ct == 0) {
201 // If it is not found in spacial args, then it is a reduce iterator.
202 // Use name to match
203 const std::string& var_name = var->name_hint;
204 for (size_t i = 0; i < reduce_axis.size(); ++i) {
205 if (var_name.find(reduce_axis[i]->var->name_hint) != std::string::npos) {
206 find_i = i;
207 find_ct++;
208 }
209 }
210 if (find_ct >= 1) {
211 if (find_i == 0) {
212 return AnnotationPosType::kPosInnerReduce;
213 } else if (find_i == reduce_axis.size() - 1) {
214 return AnnotationPosType::kPosOuterReduce;
215 } else {
216 return AnnotationPosType::kPosMiddleReduce;
217 }
218 } else {
219 // If the axis is not found in both spatial args and reduce axis,
220 // then this stage must compute_at somewhere under this axis and this axis is simplified out
221 // We assume it is an outer spatial
222 return AnnotationPosType::kPosOuterSpatial;
223 }
224 } else if (find_ct == 1) {
225 if (find_i == spatial_args.size() - 1) {
226 return AnnotationPosType::kPosInnerSpatial;
227 } else if (find_i == 0) {
228 return AnnotationPosType::kPosOuterSpatial;
229 } else {
230 return AnnotationPosType::kPosMiddleSpatial;
231 }
232 } else {
233 return AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed;
234 }
235}
236
237// Return the maximum extent of a for loop
238int64_t GetLoopExtent(const ForNode* node, const Analyzer& ana) {
239 int64_t bound = ana.const_int_bound(node->extent)->max_value;
240 if (bound == ConstIntBound::kPosInf) {
241 return 1; // Analyzer could not determine a valid bound, use 1 instead.
242 } else {
243 return bound;
244 }
245}

247// Count math ops in an expr
248class MathOpCounter : public StmtExprVisitor {
249 public:
250#define VisitBinary(Type, float_ct, int_ct) \
251 void VisitExpr_(const Type* op) final { \
252 if (op->a.dtype().is_float() || op->a.dtype().is_bfloat16()) { \
253 float_ct += op->a.dtype().lanes(); \
254 } else { \
255 int_ct += op->a.dtype().lanes(); \
256 } \
257 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op); \
258 }
259
260 VisitBinary(AddNode, float_addsub, int_addsub);
261 VisitBinary(SubNode, float_addsub, int_addsub);
262 VisitBinary(MulNode, float_mul, int_mul);
263 VisitBinary(DivNode, float_divmod, int_divmod);
264 VisitBinary(ModNode, float_divmod, int_divmod);
265 VisitBinary(FloorDivNode, float_divmod, int_divmod);
266 VisitBinary(FloorModNode, float_divmod, int_divmod);
267 VisitBinary(MaxNode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
268 VisitBinary(MinNode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
269 VisitBinary(EQNode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
270 VisitBinary(NENode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
271 VisitBinary(LTNode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
272 VisitBinary(LENode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
273 VisitBinary(GTNode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
274 VisitBinary(GENode, float_cmp, int_cmp);
275
276#undef VisitBinary
277
278 void VisitExpr_(const AndNode* op) final {
279 bool_op++;
280 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
281 }
282 void VisitExpr_(const OrNode* op) final {
283 bool_op++;
284 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
285 }
286 void VisitExpr_(const NotNode* op) final {
287 bool_op++;
288 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
289 }
290 void VisitExpr_(const SelectNode* op) final {
291 select_op++;
292 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
293 }
294
295 void VisitExpr_(const CallNode* op) final {
296 auto* pop = op->op.as<OpNode>();
297 ICHECK(pop != nullptr);
298 auto effect_kind = op_call_effect_[GetRef<Op>(pop)];
299 bool is_pure =
300 effect_kind == CallEffectKind::kPure || effect_kind == CallEffectKind::kExprAnnotation;
301
302 if (is_pure) {
303 if (op->dtype.is_float() || op->dtype.is_bfloat16()) {
304 float_math_func++;
305 } else {
306 int_math_func++;
307 }
308 } else {
309 if (op->dtype.is_float() || op->dtype.is_bfloat16()) {
310 float_other_func++;
311 } else {
312 int_other_func++;
313 }
314 }
315 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
316 }
317
318 // todo(merrymercy): Detect MAD (Multiply–add)
319 size_t float_mad{0}; // The number of float MAD (Multiply–add) ops
320 size_t float_addsub{0}; // The number of float add and sub ops
321 size_t float_mul{0}; // The number of float multiply ops
322 size_t float_divmod{0}; // The number of float div and mod ops
323 size_t float_cmp{0}; // The number of float comparison ops
324 size_t float_math_func{0}; // The number of float math func calls
325 size_t float_other_func{0}; // The number of other float func calls
326 size_t int_mad{0}; // The number of integer MAD (Multiply–add) ops
327 size_t int_addsub{0}; // The number of integer add and sub ops
328 size_t int_mul{0}; // The number of float multiply ops
329 size_t int_divmod{0}; // The number of float div and mod ops
330 size_t int_cmp{0}; // The number of float comparison ops
331 size_t int_math_func{0}; // The number of float math func calls
332 size_t int_other_func{0}; // The number of other float func calls
333 size_t bool_op{0}; // The number of bool ops
334 size_t select_op{0}; // The number of select ops
335
336 OpAttrMap<TCallEffectKind> op_call_effect_ = Op::GetAttrMap<TCallEffectKind>("TCallEffectKind");
337};

339// Extract all buffer accesses in an expr
340class BufferAccessExtractor : public StmtExprVisitor {
341 public:
342 void ExtractReads(const PrimExpr& expr) { this->VisitExpr(expr); }
343
344 void InsertAccess(const Var& buf, BufferAccessType acc_type, const Array<PrimExpr>& indices) {
345 BufferAccess& acc = buf_accesses[buf];
346 acc.acc_type = acc_type;
347 acc.indices.push_back(std::vector<PrimExpr>(indices.begin(), indices.end()));
348 }
349
350 void VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* op) final {
351 AddAccess(op->buffer->data, op->indices);
352 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(op);
353 }
354
355 void AddAccess(const Var& buffer, const Array<PrimExpr>& indices) {
356 BufferAccess& acc = buf_accesses[buffer];
357 switch (acc.acc_type) {
358 case BufferAccessType::kRead:
359 break;
360 case BufferAccessType::kWrite:
361 acc.acc_type = BufferAccessType::kReadWrite;
362 break;
363 case BufferAccessType::kReadWrite:
364 break;
365 case BufferAccessType::kUnknownRW:
366 default:
367 acc.acc_type = BufferAccessType::kRead;
368 break;
369 }
370
371 if (acc.acc_type != BufferAccessType::kReadWrite) {
372 // If a buffer is both read and written, in the tvm DSL, it must be a update,
373 // so the indices should be the same. Then we can skip appending indices for it.
374 // Otherwise we do the following.
375 buf_accesses[buffer].indices.push_back(std::vector<PrimExpr>(indices.begin(), indices.end()));
376 }
377 }
378
379 BufferMap<BufferAccess> buf_accesses;
380};

382// Compute the coefficient for an loop iterator in an expression
383// Note: we use an approximation strategy to find coefficient.
384// Hopefully, it is faster than DetectLinearEquation and can handle more cases (non-linear)
385class CoefficientExtractor : public StmtExprVisitor {
386 public:
387 void VisitExpr_(const MulNode* node) final {
388 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(node);
389 if (visited_var) {
390 if (!visited_add) {
391 if (auto a = node->a.as<IntImmNode>()) {
392 visited_mul = true;
393 stride = a->value;
394 } else if (auto b = node->b.as<IntImmNode>()) {
395 visited_mul = true;
396 stride = b->value;
397 }
398 }
399 }
400 }
401
402 void VisitExpr_(const AddNode* node) final {
403 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(node);
404 if (visited_var) {
405 if (!visited_mul) {
406 visited_add = true;
407 stride = 1;
408 }
409 }
410 }
411
412 void VisitExpr_(const VarNode* node) final {
413 if (node == var_) {
414 visited_var = true;
415 // This is a magic default stride in case our approximation strategy fails
416 stride = 2;
417 }
418 }
419
420 int ExtractCoefficient(const PrimExpr& expr, const VarNode* var) {
421 visited_var = visited_mul = visited_add = false;
422 var_ = var;
423
424 this->VisitExpr(expr);
425
426 if (visited_var && !visited_mul && !visited_add) {
427 return 1;
428 } else {
429 return stride;
430 }
431 }
432
433 bool visited_var{false};
434 bool visited_mul{false};
435 bool visited_add{false};
436 int stride{0};
437
438 private:
439 const VarNode* var_{nullptr};
440};
441
442// Compute stride for the accesses to a buffer
443int64_t ComputeStride(const std::vector<std::vector<PrimExpr>>& indices,
444 const std::vector<int>& shape, const VarNode* stride_var) {
445 int64_t min_stride = std::numeric_limits<int64_t>::max();
446 bool find = false;
447 CoefficientExtractor extractor;
448
449 for (const auto& index : indices) {
450 int64_t shape_stride = 1;
451 for (int i = static_cast<int>(index.size()) - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
452 int coefficient = extractor.ExtractCoefficient(index[i], stride_var);
453 if (extractor.visited_var) {
454 find = true;
455 min_stride = std::min(min_stride, std::abs(coefficient) * shape_stride);
456 break;
457 }
458 shape_stride *= shape[i];
459 }
460 }
461
462 return find ? min_stride : 0;
463}

465// Compute touched bytes and cache lines for accesses to a buffer
466void ComputeRegion(const std::vector<std::vector<PrimExpr>>& indices, arith::Analyzer* ana,
467 std::vector<int>* region) {
468 region->clear();
469
470 if (indices.empty()) {
471 return;
472 }
473
474 region->reserve(indices[0].size());
475
476 if (indices.size() == 1) {
477 for (const auto& index : indices[0]) {
478 ConstIntBound bound = ana->const_int_bound(index);
479 region->push_back(bound->max_value - bound->min_value + 1);
480 }
481 } else {
482 // future(lmzheng): implement a more accurate IntSet?
483 for (size_t i = 0; i < indices[0].size(); ++i) {
484 int64_t minimum = ConstIntBound::kPosInf, maximum = ConstIntBound::kNegInf;
485 for (size_t j = 0; j < indices.size(); ++j) {
486 ConstIntBound bound = ana->const_int_bound(indices[j][i]);
487
488 minimum = std::min(minimum, bound->min_value);
489 maximum = std::max(maximum, bound->max_value);
490 }
491 region->push_back(maximum - minimum + 1);
492 }
493 }
494}

496// Compute reuse distance and reuse ratio for accesses to a buffer
497// return values: reuse_type, reuse_dis_iter, reuse_dis_bytes, reuse_ct
498std::tuple<ReuseType, float, float, float> ComputeReuse(
499 const Var& buf, const std::vector<std::vector<PrimExpr>>& indices,
500 const std::vector<const ForNode*>& for_loop_stack,
501 const std::unordered_map<const ForNode*,
502 BufferMap<std::vector<std::tuple<BufferAccessType, int64_t, int>>>>&
503 for_touch_regions,
504 const Analyzer& ana) {
505 float reuse_dis_iter = 1.0f;
506 float reuse_dis_bytes = -1.0f;
507
508 for (int i = static_cast<int>(for_loop_stack.size()) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {
509 const ForNode* cur_for = for_loop_stack[i];
510 bool find = false;
511
512 for (size_t j = 0; j < indices.size(); j++) {
513 for (size_t k = 0; k < indices[j].size(); k++) {
514 if (VarInExpr(cur_for->loop_var, indices[j][k])) {
515 find = true;
516 break;
517 }
518 }
519 if (find) {
520 break;
521 }
522 }
523
524 int64_t extent = GetLoopExtent(for_loop_stack[i], ana);
525 if (find) {
526 // accumulate/update reuse distance
527 reuse_dis_iter *= extent;
528 reuse_dis_bytes = 0.0f;
529 for (const auto& iter : for_touch_regions.at(cur_for)) {
530 for (const auto& access : iter.second) {
531 reuse_dis_bytes += std::get<1>(access) * std::get<2>(access);
532 }
533 }
534 } else {
535 // Have LoopMultipleRead reuse
536 if (reuse_dis_bytes < 0) {
537 // For the reuse in the innermost axis, the above code won't be executed.
538 // So we compute bytes here
539 reuse_dis_bytes = 0.0f;
540 for (const auto& iter : for_touch_regions.at(cur_for)) {
541 for (const auto& access : iter.second) {
542 reuse_dis_bytes += 1 * std::get<2>(access);
543 }
544 }
545 }
546 return std::make_tuple(ReuseType::kLoopMultipleRead, reuse_dis_iter, reuse_dis_bytes, extent);
547 }
548
549 const BufferMap<std::vector<std::tuple<BufferAccessType, int64_t, int>>>& buffer_map =
550 for_touch_regions.at(cur_for);
551
552 int serial_reuse = static_cast<int>(buffer_map.at(buf).size()) - 1;
553 if (serial_reuse > 0) {
554 int64_t extent = GetLoopExtent(cur_for, ana);
555
556 // Have SerialMultipleReadWrite reuse
557 reuse_dis_iter = std::numeric_limits<float>::max();
558 for (const auto& acc_info : buffer_map.at(buf)) {
559 reuse_dis_iter = std::min(reuse_dis_iter, static_cast<float>(std::get<1>(acc_info)));
560 }
561
562 reuse_dis_bytes = 0.0f;
563 for (const auto& iter : for_touch_regions.at(cur_for)) {
564 for (const auto& access : iter.second) {
565 reuse_dis_bytes += std::get<1>(access) * std::get<2>(access);
566 }
567 }
568
569 return std::make_tuple(ReuseType::kSerialMultipleReadWrite, reuse_dis_iter / extent,
570 reuse_dis_bytes / extent, serial_reuse);
571 }
572 }
573
574 return std::make_tuple(ReuseType::kNoReuse, 0, 0, 0);
575}

577// Extract features for every BufferStore statement
578//
579// This visitor assumes that loop bounds do no depend on data or on parent loop
580// bounds. For example, `for i in .. { for j in range(i, ..) }` would result in
581// inaccurate features. This visitor also does not take conditionals into
582// consideration when creating features. Each branch of the conditional is
583// taken at the same time.
584class PerStoreFeatureExtractor : public StmtExprVisitor {
585 public:
586 explicit PerStoreFeatureExtractor(int cache_line_size, const Map<Var, Buffer>& existing_buffers)
587 : cache_line_size_(cache_line_size) {
588 for (const auto& buffer : existing_buffers) {
589 buffer_shapes[buffer.first] = buffer.second->shape;
590 buffer_dtypes[buffer.first] = buffer.second->dtype;
591 // Also need to add a reference from the buffers internal variable. This
592 // is usually how buffers are referenced within the body of a PrimFunc
593 buffer_shapes[buffer.second->data] = buffer.second->shape;
594 buffer_dtypes[buffer.second->data] = buffer.second->dtype;
595 }
596 }
597
598 void VisitStmt_(const AttrStmtNode* node) final {
599 if (node->attr_key == tir::attr::thread_extent || node->attr_key == tir::attr::virtual_thread) {
600 const Var& var = node->node.as<IterVarNode>()->var;
601 int extent = GetIntImm(node->value);
602
603 int* plen = nullptr;
604
605 const std::string& name = var.get()->name_hint;
606 if (node->attr_key == tir::attr::thread_extent) {
607 if (name == "blockIdx.x") {
608 plen = &blockIdx_x_len_;
609 } else if (name == "blockIdx.y") {
610 plen = &block_idx_y_len_;
611 } else if (name == "blockIdx.z") {
612 plen = &block_idx_z_len_;
613 } else if (name == "threadIdx.x") {
614 plen = &threadIdx_x_len_;
615 } else if (name == "threadIdx.y") {
616 plen = &thread_idx_y_len_;
617 } else if (name == "threadIdx.z") {
618 plen = &thread_idx_z_len_;
619 } else {
620 LOG(FATAL) << "invalid thread itervar " + name;
621 }
622 } else {
623 plen = &vthread_len_;
624 }
625
626 int extent_before = *plen;
627 if (node->attr_key == tir::attr::thread_extent) {
628 *plen = extent;
629 } else {
630 *plen *= extent;
631 }
632
633 is_gpu_ = true;
634
635 // make a fake for node for blockIdx.x or threadIdx.x
636 Stmt fake_for_node = For(var, 0, extent, ForKind::kParallel, node->body);
637
638 outer_loop_prod_ *= extent;
639 for_loop_stack_.push_back(fake_for_node.as<ForNode>());
640 variable_definition_stack_.push_back({});
641 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(node);
642 variable_definition_stack_.pop_back();
643 for_loop_stack_.pop_back();
644 outer_loop_prod_ /= extent;
645
646 *plen = extent_before;
647 } else if (node->attr_key == "pragma_auto_unroll_max_step") {
648 int value = GetIntImm(node->value);
649
650 int16_t old_value = cur_auto_unroll_max_step_;
651 cur_auto_unroll_max_step_ = value;
652 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(node);
653 cur_auto_unroll_max_step_ = old_value;
654 } else {
655 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(node);
656 }
657 }
658
659 void VisitStmt_(const ForNode* node) final {
660 ana_.Bind(node->loop_var, Range::FromMinExtent(node->min, node->extent));
661 int64_t loop_extent = GetLoopExtent(node, ana_);
662
663 if (node->kind == ForKind::kVectorized) {
664 vec_for_stack_.push_back(node);
665 } else if (node->kind == ForKind::kUnrolled) {
666 unroll_for_stack_.push_back(node);
667 } else if (node->kind == ForKind::kParallel) {
668 parallel_for_stack_.push_back(node);
669 }
670
671 outer_loop_prod_ *= loop_extent;
672 for_loop_stack_.push_back(node);
673 variable_definition_stack_.push_back({});
674 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(node);
675 variable_definition_stack_.pop_back();
676 for_loop_stack_.pop_back();
677 outer_loop_prod_ /= loop_extent;
678
679 if (node->kind == ForKind::kVectorized) {
680 vec_for_stack_.pop_back();
681 } else if (node->kind == ForKind::kUnrolled) {
682 unroll_for_stack_.pop_back();
683 } else if (node->kind == ForKind::kParallel) {
684 parallel_for_stack_.pop_back();
685 }
686 }

688 void VisitExpr_(const BufferLoadNode* node) final {
689 // Store buffer shape/dtype. It may already be stored.
690 buffer_shapes[node->buffer->data] = node->buffer->shape;
691 buffer_dtypes[node->buffer->data] = node->buffer->dtype;
692 StmtExprVisitor::VisitExpr_(node);
693 }
694
695 void VisitStmt_(const BufferStoreNode* node) final {
696 // Store buffer shape/dtype. It may already be stored.
697 buffer_shapes[node->buffer->data] = node->buffer->shape;
698 buffer_dtypes[node->buffer->data] = node->buffer->dtype;
699
700 MathOpCounter math_op_counter;
701 math_op_counter(node->value);
702 std::vector<float> mem_bytes_list;
703 std::vector<float> compute_ops_list;
704 double cur_compute_ops;
705
706 // Group 1: Computation related features
707 ExtractComputationFeature(node->buffer->data, node->indices, math_op_counter);
708
709 // Group 2: Buffer access related features (per buffer)
710 ExtractBufferAccessFeature(node->buffer->data, node->indices, node->value, math_op_counter,
711 &cur_compute_ops, &compute_ops_list, &mem_bytes_list);
712
713 // Group 3: Arithmetic intensity related features
714 ExtractArithmeticIntensityFeature(node->buffer->data, cur_compute_ops, compute_ops_list,
715 mem_bytes_list);
716
717 // Group 4: Allocation related features
718 ExtractOuterScopeFeature(node->buffer->data);
719 }

723 buffer_shapes[node->buffer->data] = node->buffer->shape;
724 buffer_dtypes[node->buffer->data] = node->buffer->dtype;
725 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(node);
726
727 // Group 5: Outer scope related features
728 ExtractAllocationFeature(node);
729 }

738 }

744 << "Variable definition outside of a for loop is not handled by feature extraction";

746 StmtExprVisitor::VisitStmt_(node);

749 // Extract computation related features (group 1)
750 void ExtractComputationFeature(const Var& buffer, const Array<PrimExpr>& indices,
751 const MathOpCounter& math_op_counter) {
752 FeatureSet& fea = buffer_features[buffer];
753
754 // Computation related features
755 fea.float_mad += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_mad;
756 fea.float_addsub += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_addsub;
757 fea.float_mul += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_mul;
758 fea.float_divmod += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_divmod;
759 fea.float_cmp += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_cmp;
760 fea.float_math_func += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_math_func;
761 fea.float_other_func += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.float_other_func;
762 fea.int_mad += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_mad;
763 fea.int_addsub += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_addsub;
764 fea.int_mul += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_mul;
765 fea.int_divmod += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_divmod;
766 fea.int_math_func += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_math_func;
767 fea.int_cmp += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_cmp;
768 fea.int_other_func += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.int_other_func;
769 fea.bool_op += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.bool_op;
770 fea.select_op += outer_loop_prod_ * math_op_counter.select_op;
771
772 fea.vec_len = fea.unroll_len = fea.parallel_len = 0.0f;
773 fea.vec_type = fea.unroll_type = fea.parallel_type = AnnotationPosType::kPosNone;
774
775 fea.vec_num = vec_for_stack_.size();
776 if (!vec_for_stack_.empty()) {
777 fea.vec_len = GetLoopExtent(vec_for_stack_.back(), ana_);
778 fea.vec_prod = 1.0;
779 for (const ForNode* pfor : vec_for_stack_) {
780 fea.vec_prod *= GetLoopExtent(pfor, ana_);
781 }
782 fea.vec_type = AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed;
783 // todo(merrymercy): this feature requires operation (tvm.compute) information
784 // GetAnnotationPosEncoding(vec_for_stack_.back()->loop_var,
785 // node->args, pcompute->axis, pcompute->reduce_axis);
786 }
787
788 fea.unroll_num = unroll_for_stack_.size();
789 if (!unroll_for_stack_.empty()) {
790 fea.unroll_len = GetLoopExtent(unroll_for_stack_.back(), ana_);
791 fea.unroll_prod = 1.0;
792 for (const ForNode* pfor : unroll_for_stack_) {
793 fea.unroll_prod *= GetLoopExtent(pfor, ana_);
794 }
795 fea.unroll_type = AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed;
796 // GetAnnotationPosEncoding(unroll_for_stack_.back()->loop_var,
797 // node->args, pcompute->axis, pcompute->reduce_axis);
798 }
799
800 fea.parallel_num = parallel_for_stack_.size();
801 if (!parallel_for_stack_.empty()) {
802 fea.parallel_len = GetLoopExtent(parallel_for_stack_.back(), ana_);
803 fea.parallel_prod = 1.0;
804 for (const ForNode* pfor : parallel_for_stack_) {
805 fea.parallel_prod *= GetLoopExtent(pfor, ana_);
806 }
807 fea.parallel_type = AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed;
808 // GetAnnotationPosEncoding(parallel_for_stack_.back()->loop_var,
809 // node->args, pcompute->axis, pcompute->reduce_axis);
810 }
811
812 // GPU threads
813 fea.is_gpu = is_gpu_;
814 fea.blockIdx_x_len = blockIdx_x_len_;
815 fea.blockIdx_y_len = block_idx_y_len_;
816 fea.blockIdx_z_len = block_idx_z_len_;
817 fea.threadIdx_x_len = threadIdx_x_len_;
818 fea.threadIdx_y_len = thread_idx_y_len_;
819 fea.threadIdx_z_len = thread_idx_z_len_;
820 fea.vthread_len = vthread_len_;
821 }

823 // Extract buffer access related features (group 2)
824 void ExtractBufferAccessFeature(const Var& buffer, const Array<PrimExpr>& indices,
825 const PrimExpr& value, const MathOpCounter& math_op_counter,
826 double* cur_compute_ops, std::vector<float>* compute_ops_list,
827 std::vector<float>* mem_bytes_list) {
828 FeatureSet& fea = buffer_features[buffer];
829
830 // Extract all buffer accesses
831 std::vector<BufferAccessFeature> acc_feas;
832 BufferAccessExtractor buf_extractor;
833 buf_extractor.InsertAccess(buffer, BufferAccessType::kWrite, indices);
834 buf_extractor.ExtractReads(value);
835
836 mem_bytes_list->reserve(for_loop_stack_.size());
837 compute_ops_list->reserve(for_loop_stack_.size());
838
839 *cur_compute_ops = math_op_counter.float_mad + math_op_counter.float_addsub +
840 math_op_counter.float_mul + math_op_counter.float_divmod +
841 math_op_counter.float_cmp + math_op_counter.float_math_func +
842 math_op_counter.float_other_func;
843
844 ICHECK_EQ(for_loop_stack_.size(), variable_definition_stack_.size())
845 << "variable_definition_stack_ should mirror for_loop_stack_ in size";
846 std::vector<int> tmp_region;
847 for (int i = static_cast<int>(for_loop_stack_.size()) - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
848 const ForNode* p_for = for_loop_stack_[i];
849
850 // Construct a local analyzer context which contains definitions (for and
851 // let) from innermost loops up to and including `i`. For loop variable
852 // definitions in loops more outer than `i` are set to 1 so that we can
853 // get per-loop-iteration features. Note that we add these definitions
854 // from outermost to innermost because inner definitions may depend on
855 // outer ones.
856 Analyzer local_analyzer;
857 for (int j = 0; j < i; j++) {
858 local_analyzer.Bind(for_loop_stack_.at(j)->loop_var,
859 Range::FromMinExtent(for_loop_stack_.at(j)->min, 1));
860 }
861 for (int j = i; j < static_cast<int>(for_loop_stack_.size()); j++) {
862 local_analyzer.Bind(
863 for_loop_stack_.at(j)->loop_var,
864 Range::FromMinExtent(for_loop_stack_.at(j)->min, for_loop_stack_.at(j)->extent));
865 for (auto definition : variable_definition_stack_.at(j)) {
866 local_analyzer.Bind(std::get<0>(definition), std::get<1>(definition));
867 }
868 }
869
870 // Note, here we do overwrite.
871 // So if there are multiple BufferStoreNode, the last one will overwrite the first few.
872 // e.g. The update part in gemm will overwrite the init part.
873 BufferMap<std::vector<std::tuple<BufferAccessType, int64_t, int>>>& buffer_regions_map =
874 for_touch_regions_[p_for];
875
876 int64_t mem_bytes = 0;
877 for (const auto& x : buf_extractor.buf_accesses) {
878 const Var& t = x.first;
879 const BufferAccess& acc = x.second;
880
881 ComputeRegion(acc.indices, &local_analyzer, &tmp_region);
882 int64_t touched_size = ElementProduct(tmp_region);
883 buffer_regions_map[t].push_back(
884 std::make_tuple(acc.acc_type, touched_size, buffer_dtypes.at(t).bytes()));
885 mem_bytes += touched_size * buffer_dtypes.at(t).bytes();
886 }
887
888 mem_bytes_list->push_back(mem_bytes);
889 *cur_compute_ops *= GetLoopExtent(for_loop_stack_[i], local_analyzer);
890 compute_ops_list->push_back(*cur_compute_ops);
891 }
892
893 // Buffer access related features (per buffer)
894 for (const auto& x : buf_extractor.buf_accesses) {
895 const Var& t = x.first;
896 const BufferAccess& acc = x.second;
897
898 std::vector<int> int_shape;
899 for (const auto& dim : buffer_shapes.at(t)) {
900 int_shape.push_back(GetIntImm(dim));
901 }
902
903 size_t ele_bytes = buffer_dtypes.at(t).bytes();
904
905 // calculate bytes
906 float bytes = outer_loop_prod_ * ele_bytes;
907 float unique_bytes;
908
909 // calculate cache lines
910 int64_t stride;
911 float lines;
912 float unique_lines;
913
914 if (for_loop_stack_.empty()) {
915 unique_bytes = ele_bytes;
916 stride = 0;
917 lines = 1.0f;
918 unique_lines = 1.0f;
919 } else {
920 unique_bytes =
921 std::get<1>(for_touch_regions_[for_loop_stack_.front()][t].front()) * ele_bytes;
922
923 stride = 0;
924 int64_t reduce_ratio = 1;
925
926 int i;
927 for (i = static_cast<int>(for_loop_stack_.size()) - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
928 stride = ComputeStride(acc.indices, int_shape, for_loop_stack_[i]->loop_var.get());
929 if (stride != 0) {
930 break;
931 }
932 reduce_ratio *= GetLoopExtent(for_loop_stack_.back(), ana_);
933 }
934
935 lines = outer_loop_prod_ / reduce_ratio *
936 std::min(1.0f, 1.0f * stride * ele_bytes / cache_line_size_);
937 lines = std::max(lines, 1.0f);
938
939 // convert `stride` back to the stride of the innermost iterator
940 stride = (i == static_cast<int>(for_loop_stack_.size()) - 1 ? stride : 0);
941
942 float n_continuous = ele_bytes;
943 for (int i = std::min(static_cast<int>(tmp_region.size()) - 1,
944 static_cast<int>(int_shape.size()) - 1);
945 i >= 0; i--) {
946 if (tmp_region[i] == int_shape[i]) {
947 n_continuous *= tmp_region[i];
948 break;
949 }
950 }
951 unique_lines = unique_bytes / std::min(n_continuous, static_cast<float>(cache_line_size_));
952 unique_lines = std::max(unique_lines, 1.0f);
953 }
954
955 auto [reuse_type, reuse_dis_iter, reuse_dis_bytes, reuse_ct] =
956 ComputeReuse(t, acc.indices, for_loop_stack_, for_touch_regions_, ana_);
957
958 acc_feas.emplace_back();
959 BufferAccessFeature& acc_fea = acc_feas.back();
960
961 // TODO(tkonolige): save buffer names and use those instead?
962 acc_fea.buffer_name = t->name_hint;
963 acc_fea.acc_type = acc.acc_type;
964 acc_fea.stride = stride;
965 acc_fea.bytes = bytes;
966 acc_fea.unique_bytes = unique_bytes;
967 acc_fea.lines = lines;
968 acc_fea.unique_lines = unique_lines;
969 acc_fea.reuse_type = reuse_type;
970 acc_fea.reuse_dis_iter = reuse_dis_iter;
971 acc_fea.reuse_dis_bytes = reuse_dis_bytes;
972 acc_fea.reuse_ct = reuse_ct;
973 if (acc_fea.reuse_ct > 0.5) {
974 acc_fea.bytes_d_reuse_ct = bytes / reuse_ct;
975 acc_fea.unique_bytes_d_reuse_ct = unique_bytes / reuse_ct;
976 acc_fea.lines_d_reuse_ct = lines / reuse_ct;
977 acc_fea.unique_lines_d_reuse_ct = unique_lines / reuse_ct;
978 } else {
979 // no reuse, multiply by a magic number '2'
980 acc_fea.bytes_d_reuse_ct = bytes * 2;
981 acc_fea.unique_bytes_d_reuse_ct = unique_bytes * 2;
982 acc_fea.lines_d_reuse_ct = lines * 2;
983 acc_fea.unique_lines_d_reuse_ct = unique_lines * 2;
984 }
985 }
986
987 fea.access_feas = acc_feas;
988 }
989
990 // Extract arithmetic intensity related feature (group 3)
991 void ExtractArithmeticIntensityFeature(const Var& buffer, double cur_compute_ops,
992 const std::vector<float>& compute_ops_list,
993 const std::vector<float>& mem_bytes_list) {
994 FeatureSet& fea = buffer_features[buffer];
995
996 // Compute arithmetic intensity curve (y axis : arithmetic intensity, x axis : flops).
997 // We use piecewise linear interpolation to fit this curve.
998 int pt = 0;
999 if (cur_compute_ops <= 0 || compute_ops_list.empty()) {
1000 std::fill(fea.arith_intensity_curve,
1001 fea.arith_intensity_curve + ARITH_INTENSITY_CURVE_SAMPLE_N, 0.0);
1002 } else {
1003 for (size_t i = 0; i < ARITH_INTENSITY_CURVE_SAMPLE_N; ++i) {
1004 float cur_compute_ops = compute_ops_list.back() * (i + 1) / ARITH_INTENSITY_CURVE_SAMPLE_N;
1005 while (compute_ops_list[pt] < cur_compute_ops - 1e-4) {
1006 pt++;
1007 }
1008 ICHECK_LT(pt, compute_ops_list.size());
1009
1010 float value;
1011 if (pt == 0) {
1012 value = compute_ops_list[pt] / mem_bytes_list[pt];
1013 } else {
1014 float base = compute_ops_list[pt - 1] / mem_bytes_list[pt - 1];
1015 float slope = (compute_ops_list[pt] / mem_bytes_list[pt] -
1016 compute_ops_list[pt - 1] / mem_bytes_list[pt - 1]) /
1017 (compute_ops_list[pt] - compute_ops_list[pt - 1]);
1018 value = base + slope * (cur_compute_ops - compute_ops_list[pt - 1]);
1019 }
1020 fea.arith_intensity_curve[i] = value;
1021 }
1022 }
1023 }

1025 // Extract allocation related features (group 4)
1026 void ExtractAllocationFeature(const BufferRealizeNode* node) {
1027 FeatureSet& fea = buffer_features[node->buffer->data];
1028
1029 float allocation_size = 1.0f;
1030 for (const auto& x : node->bounds) {
1031 allocation_size *= GetIntImm(x->extent);
1032 }
1033 // allocation feature
1034 fea.alloc_size = allocation_size * node->buffer->dtype.bytes();
1035 fea.alloc_prod = allocation_size * outer_loop_prod_;
1036 fea.alloc_outer_prod = outer_loop_prod_;
1037 fea.alloc_inner_prod = fea.outer_prod / outer_loop_prod_;
1038 }
1039
1040 void ExtractAllocationFeature(const AllocateNode* node) {
1041 FeatureSet& fea = buffer_features[node->buffer_var];
1042
1043 float allocation_size = 1.0f;
1044 for (const auto& x : node->extents) {
1045 // TODO(tkonolige): will not handle dynamic shape
1046 allocation_size *= GetIntImm(x);
1047 }
1048 // allocation feature
1049 fea.alloc_size = allocation_size * node->dtype.bytes();
1050 fea.alloc_prod = allocation_size * outer_loop_prod_;
1051 fea.alloc_outer_prod = outer_loop_prod_;
1052 fea.alloc_inner_prod = fea.outer_prod / outer_loop_prod_;
1053 }

1055 // Extract outer scope related features (group 5)
1056 void ExtractOuterScopeFeature(const Var& buffer) {
1057 FeatureSet& fea = buffer_features[buffer];
1058
1059 fea.outer_prod = outer_loop_prod_;
1060 fea.num_loops = for_loop_stack_.size();
1061 fea.auto_unroll_max_step = cur_auto_unroll_max_step_;
1062 }

1065 BufferMap<FeatureSet> buffer_features;

1067 private:
1068 // The shared arithmetic analyzer
1069 Analyzer ana_;
1070
1071 // The product of outer loop
1072 float outer_loop_prod_ = 1.0f;
1073
1074 // The stacks to store parent loops during DFS
1075 std::vector<const ForNode*> for_loop_stack_;
1076 std::vector<const ForNode*> parallel_for_stack_;
1077 std::vector<const ForNode*> vec_for_stack_;
1078 std::vector<const ForNode*> unroll_for_stack_;
1079 std::vector<std::vector<std::tuple<Var, PrimExpr>>> variable_definition_stack_;
1080
1081 // GPU-related features
1082 bool is_gpu_{false};
1083 int blockIdx_x_len_{1};
1084 int block_idx_y_len_{1};
1085 int block_idx_z_len_{1};
1086 int threadIdx_x_len_{1};
1087 int thread_idx_y_len_{1};
1088 int thread_idx_z_len_{1};
1089 int vthread_len_{1};
1090 int16_t cur_auto_unroll_max_step_{0};
1091
1092 // Store touch region information for all for loops. The format of this nested map:
1093 // For a loop, for all its touched buffers, for all different accesses to the buffers,
1094 // its (access type, number of touched elements, number of bytes of single element)
1095 std::unordered_map<const ForNode*,
1096 BufferMap<std::vector<std::tuple<BufferAccessType, int64_t, int>>>>
1097 for_touch_regions_;
1098
1099 // The default cache line size in bytes
1100 const int cache_line_size_ = 64;
1101
1102 // Storage of buffer shape and dtype information. Needed because Load/Store
1103 // nodes only do not contain this information.
1104 BufferMap<Array<PrimExpr>> buffer_shapes;
1105 BufferMap<DataType> buffer_dtypes;
1106};

1108// shifted log to incorporate the property that log2p(0) = 0
1109inline float log2p(float x) { return x < 0 ? -std::log2(-x + 1) : std::log2(x + 1); }
1110
1111void GetPerStoreFeature(const PrimFunc& func, int cache_line_size, int max_n_bufs,
1112 std::vector<float>* ret, bool log_scale) {
1113 PerStoreFeatureExtractor extractor(cache_line_size, func->buffer_map);
1114 extractor(func->body);
1115
1116 auto slog = log_scale ? log2p : [](float x) { return x; };
1117
1118 ret->push_back(extractor.buffer_features.size());
1119
1120 for (const auto& x : extractor.buffer_features) {
1121 const FeatureSet& fea_set = x.second;
1122
1123 /***** Group 1: Computation related features *****/
1124 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_mad));
1125 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_addsub));
1126 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_mul));
1127 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_divmod));
1128 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_cmp));
1129 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_math_func));
1130 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.float_other_func));
1131 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_mad));
1132 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_addsub));
1133 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_mul));
1134 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_divmod));
1135 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_cmp));
1136 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_math_func));
1137 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.int_other_func));
1138 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.bool_op));
1139 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.select_op));
1140
1141 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.vec_num));
1142 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.vec_prod));
1143 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.vec_len));
1144 for (int i = 0; i <= static_cast<int>(AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed); i++) {
1145 ret->push_back(i == static_cast<int>(fea_set.vec_type));
1146 }
1147
1148 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.unroll_num));
1149 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.unroll_prod));
1150 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.unroll_len));
1151 for (int i = 0; i <= static_cast<int>(AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed); i++) {
1152 ret->push_back(i == static_cast<int>(fea_set.unroll_type));
1153 }
1154
1155 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.parallel_num));
1156 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.parallel_prod));
1157 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.parallel_len));
1158 for (int i = 0; i <= static_cast<int>(AnnotationPosType::kPosMixed); i++) {
1159 ret->push_back(i == static_cast<int>(fea_set.parallel_type));
1160 }
1161
1162 ret->push_back(fea_set.is_gpu);
1163 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.blockIdx_x_len));
1164 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.blockIdx_y_len));
1165 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.blockIdx_z_len));
1166 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.threadIdx_x_len));
1167 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.threadIdx_y_len));
1168 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.threadIdx_z_len));
1169 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.vthread_len));
1170
1171 /***** Group 2: Buffer access related features *****/
1172 // sort according to pair (lines, bytes)
1173 std::vector<std::pair<float, float>> buf_order_key;
1174 for (const auto& acc_fea : fea_set.access_feas) {
1175 buf_order_key.emplace_back(acc_fea.lines, acc_fea.bytes);
1176 }
1177 std::vector<int> buf_order(buf_order_key.size());
1178 std::iota(buf_order.begin(), buf_order.end(), 0);
1179
1180 auto cmp = [&buf_order_key](int l, int r) {
1181 return buf_order_key[l].first > buf_order_key[r].first ||
1182 (buf_order_key[l].first == buf_order_key[r].first &&
1183 buf_order_key[l].second > buf_order_key[r].second);
1184 };
1185 std::sort(buf_order.begin(), buf_order.end(), cmp);
1186 int n_bufs = std::min(max_n_bufs, static_cast<int>(buf_order.size()));
1187 buf_order.resize(n_bufs);
1188
1189 for (int idx : buf_order) {
1190 const auto& acc_fea = fea_set.access_feas[idx];
1191 for (int j = 0; j <= static_cast<int>(BufferAccessType::kReadWrite); ++j) {
1192 ret->push_back(j == static_cast<int>(acc_fea.acc_type));
1193 }
1194 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.bytes));
1195 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.unique_bytes));
1196 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.lines));
1197 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.unique_lines));
1198 for (int j = 0; j <= static_cast<int>(ReuseType::kNoReuse); ++j) {
1199 ret->push_back(j == static_cast<int>(acc_fea.reuse_type));
1200 }
1201 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.reuse_dis_iter));
1202 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.reuse_dis_bytes));
1203 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.reuse_ct));
1204 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.bytes_d_reuse_ct));
1205 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.unique_bytes_d_reuse_ct));
1206 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.lines_d_reuse_ct));
1207 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.unique_lines_d_reuse_ct));
1208 ret->push_back(slog(acc_fea.stride));
1209 }
1210 // - fill padding
1211 for (int i = 0; i < max_n_bufs - n_bufs; ++i) {
1212 for (int j = 0; j <= static_cast<int>(BufferAccessType::kReadWrite); ++j) { // 3
1213 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1214 }
1215 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1216 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1217 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1218 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1219 for (int j = 0; j <= static_cast<int>(ReuseType::kNoReuse); ++j) { // 3
1220 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1221 }
1222 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1223 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1224 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1225 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1226 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1227 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1228 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1229 ret->push_back(0.0f);
1230 }
1231
1232 /***** Group 3: Arithmetic intensity related features *****/
1233 for (size_t i = 0; i < ARITH_INTENSITY_CURVE_SAMPLE_N; ++i) {
1234 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.arith_intensity_curve[i]));
1235 }
1236
1237 /***** Group 4: Allocation related features *****/
1238 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.alloc_size));
1239 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.alloc_prod));
1240 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.alloc_outer_prod));
1241 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.alloc_inner_prod));
1242
1243 /***** Group 5: Outer scope related features *****/
1244 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.outer_prod));
1245 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.num_loops));
1246 ret->push_back(slog(fea_set.auto_unroll_max_step));
1247 }
1248}

1355void GetPerStoreFeaturesWorkerFunc(const SearchTask& task, const State& state, int max_n_bufs,
1356 std::vector<float>* feature, std::atomic<int>* error_ct) {
1357 auto [sch, tensors] = task->compute_dag.ApplySteps(state->transform_steps);
1358
1359 // When inlining, replace const matrices with const values.
1360 // Produces wrong IR, but good enough for feature extraction, and
1361 // can improve the speed of feature extraction/search. Must be
1362 // called before ScheduleToModule to have an effect.
1363 sch = sch.normalize_for_feature_extraction();
1364
1365 try {
1366 const std::string& name = "main";
1367 auto pass_ctx = tvm::transform::PassContext::Current();
1368
1369 auto mod = ScheduleToModule(sch, Array<ObjectRef>{tensors.begin(), tensors.end()}, name,
1370 std::unordered_map<te::Tensor, te::Buffer>(),
1371 GlobalVarSupply(NameSupply("")));
1372
1373 bool disable_vectorize =
1374 pass_ctx->GetConfig<Bool>("tir.disable_vectorize", Bool(false)).value();
1375 bool instrument_bound_checkers =
1376 pass_ctx->GetConfig<Bool>("tir.instrument_bound_checkers", Bool(false)).value();
1377
1378 if (IsGPUTask(task)) {
1379 auto pass_list = Array<tvm::transform::Pass>();
1380 // Phase 0
1381 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::InjectPrefetch());
1382 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::StorageFlatten(64, instrument_bound_checkers));
1383 // Phase 1
1384 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::NarrowDataType(32));
1385 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::Simplify());
1386 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::VectorizeLoop(!disable_vectorize));
1387 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::InjectVirtualThread());
1388 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::StorageRewrite());
1389 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::Simplify());
1390 tvm::Map<String, tvm::PrimExpr> gpu_params{
1391 {"max_shared_memory_per_block", task->hardware_params->max_shared_memory_per_block},
1392 {"max_local_memory_per_block", task->hardware_params->max_local_memory_per_block},
1393 {"max_threads_per_block", task->hardware_params->max_threads_per_block},
1394 {"max_vector_bytes", task->hardware_params->vector_unit_bytes},
1395 {"max_vthread", task->hardware_params->max_vthread_extent},
1396 };
1397 pass_list.push_back(tir::transform::VerifyGPUCode(gpu_params));
1398 const auto& optimize = tir::transform::Sequential(pass_list);
1399 optimize(mod);
1400 }
1401 const auto& optimize =
1402 tir::transform::Sequential(Array<tvm::transform::Pass>{tir::transform::Simplify()});
1403 mod = optimize(std::move(mod));
1404 PrimFunc prim_func = Downcast<PrimFunc>(mod->Lookup(name));
1405 GetPerStoreFeature(prim_func, task->hardware_params->cache_line_bytes, max_n_bufs, feature);
1406 } catch (Error& e) {
1407 (*error_ct)++;
1408 }
1409}

1411void GetPerStoreFeaturesFromStates(const Array<State>& states, const SearchTask& task,
1412 int skip_first_n_feature_extraction, int max_n_bufs,
1413 std::vector<std::vector<float>>* features) {
1414 // extract features
1415 features->assign(states.size(), std::vector<float>());
1416
1417 std::atomic<int> error_ct(0);
1418
1419 support::parallel_for(skip_first_n_feature_extraction, states.size(),
1420 [&task, &states, &max_n_bufs, &features, &error_ct](int i) {
1421 GetPerStoreFeaturesWorkerFunc(task, states[i], max_n_bufs,
1422 &(*features)[i], &error_ct);
1423 });
1424}

1441void GetPerStoreFeaturesFromFile(const std::string& filename, int max_lines, int max_n_bufs,
1442 std::vector<std::vector<float>>* features,
1443 std::vector<float>* normalized_throughputs,
1444 std::vector<int>* task_ids) {
1445 Array<State> states;
1446 std::vector<SearchTask> tasks;
1447
1448 normalized_throughputs->clear();
1449 task_ids->clear();
1450
1451 // (workload_key, target) -> (search_task, task_id)
1452 std::unordered_map<std::pair<std::string, std::string>, std::pair<SearchTask, size_t>> task_cache;
1453 // task_id -> min_cost
1454 std::vector<float> min_costs;
1455
1456 const auto* workload_key_to_tensors =
1457 tvm::runtime::Registry::Get("auto_scheduler.workload_key_to_tensors");
1458 ICHECK(workload_key_to_tensors != nullptr);
1459
1460 // read from file
1461 RecordReader reader(filename);
1462 auto cur_inp = make_object<MeasureInputNode>();
1463 auto cur_res = make_object<MeasureResultNode>();
1464 while (reader->ReadNext(cur_inp.get(), cur_res.get())) {
1465 float cost = static_cast<float>(FloatArrayMean(cur_res->costs));
1466 const std::string& workload_key = cur_inp->task->workload_key;
1467
1468 SearchTask task;
1469 size_t task_id;
1470 std::pair<std::string, std::string> key(workload_key, cur_inp->task->target->str());
1471 auto find_res = task_cache.find(key);
1472 if (find_res == task_cache.end()) {
1473 // rebuild task
1474 Array<te::Tensor> tensors = (*workload_key_to_tensors)(workload_key);
1475 Target target = cur_inp->task->target;
1476 Target target_host = cur_inp->task->target_host;
1477 CheckAndUpdateHostConsistency(&target, &target_host);
1478 task = SearchTask(ComputeDAG(tensors), workload_key, target, target_host,
1479 cur_inp->task->hardware_params, cur_inp->task->layout_rewrite_option,
1480 cur_inp->task->task_input_names);
1481 task_id = task_cache.size();
1482
1483 // compute min cost for each task
1484 task_cache.insert(std::make_pair(key, std::make_pair(task, task_id)));
1485 min_costs.push_back(cost);
1486 } else {
1487 std::tie(task, task_id) = find_res->second;
1488 min_costs[task_id] = std::min(min_costs[task_id], cost);
1489 }
1490
1491 tasks.push_back(std::move(task));
1492 task_ids->push_back(task_id);
1493 states.push_back(cur_inp->state);
1494 normalized_throughputs->push_back(cost);
1495
1496 if (max_lines > 0 && static_cast<int>(states.size()) >= max_lines) {
1497 break;
1498 }
1499 }
1500
1501 for (size_t i = 0; i < normalized_throughputs->size(); ++i) {
1502 (*normalized_throughputs)[i] = min_costs[(*task_ids)[i]] / (*normalized_throughputs)[i];
1503 }
1504
1505 GetPerStoreFeaturesFromStates(states, tasks, 0, max_n_bufs, features);
1506}

1508void GetPerStoreFeaturesFromMeasurePairs(const Array<MeasureInput>& inputs,
1509 const Array<MeasureResult>& results,
1510 int skip_first_n_feature_extraction, int max_n_bufs,
1511 std::vector<std::vector<float>>* features,
1512 std::vector<float>* normalized_throughputs,
1513 std::vector<int>* task_ids) {
1514 Array<State> states;
1515 std::vector<SearchTask> tasks;
1516
1517 normalized_throughputs->clear();
1518 task_ids->clear();
1519
1520 // (workload_key, target) -> (search_task, task_id)
1521 std::unordered_map<std::pair<std::string, std::string>, std::pair<SearchTask, size_t>> task_cache;
1522 // task_id -> min_cost
1523 std::vector<float> min_costs;
1524
1525 const auto* workload_key_to_tensors =
1526 tvm::runtime::Registry::Get("auto_scheduler.workload_key_to_tensors");
1527 ICHECK(workload_key_to_tensors != nullptr);
1528
1529 tasks.reserve(inputs.size());
1530 normalized_throughputs->reserve(inputs.size());
1531 task_ids->reserve(inputs.size());
1532 for (size_t i = 0; i < inputs.size(); ++i) {
1533 float cost = static_cast<float>(FloatArrayMean(results[i]->costs));
1534 const std::string& workload_key = inputs[i]->task->workload_key;
1535 SearchTask task;
1536
1537 size_t task_id;
1538 std::pair<std::string, std::string> key(workload_key, inputs[i]->task->target->str());
1539 auto find_res = task_cache.find(key);
1540 if (find_res == task_cache.end()) {
1541 if (inputs[i]->task->compute_dag.defined()) { // the measure input is complete
1542 task = inputs[i]->task;
1543 } else {
1544 // The measure input is incomplete, rebuild task for incomplete measure pairs read from file
1545 try {
1546 Array<te::Tensor> tensors = (*workload_key_to_tensors)(workload_key);
1547 Target target = inputs[i]->task->target;
1548 Target target_host = inputs[i]->task->target_host;
1549 CheckAndUpdateHostConsistency(&target, &target_host);
1550 task =
1551 SearchTask(ComputeDAG(tensors), workload_key, target, target_host,
1552 inputs[i]->task->hardware_params, inputs[i]->task->layout_rewrite_option,
1553 inputs[i]->task->task_input_names);
1554 } catch (std::exception& e) {
1555 // Cannot build ComputeDAG from workload key, the task may have not been registered in
1556 // this search round
1557 continue;
1558 }
1559 }
1560 task_id = task_cache.size();
1561
1562 // compute min cost for each task
1563 task_cache.insert(std::make_pair(key, std::make_pair(task, task_id)));
1564 min_costs.push_back(cost);
1565 } else {
1566 std::tie(task, task_id) = find_res->second;
1567 min_costs[task_id] = std::min(min_costs[task_id], cost);
1568 }
1569
1570 tasks.push_back(std::move(task));
1571 task_ids->push_back(task_id);
1572 states.push_back(inputs[i]->state);
1573 normalized_throughputs->push_back(cost);
1574 }
1575
1576 for (size_t i = 0; i < normalized_throughputs->size(); ++i) {
1577 (*normalized_throughputs)[i] = min_costs[(*task_ids)[i]] / (*normalized_throughputs)[i];
1578 }
1579
1580 GetPerStoreFeaturesFromStates(states, tasks, skip_first_n_feature_extraction, max_n_bufs,
1581 features);
1582}

1584/*
1585 * \brief Serialize a two-dimensional variable-size feature vector with normalized throughputs
1586 * and task ids to a one-dimensional flatten byte array.
1587 *
1588 * For faster data copy between c++ and python, the c++ part returns features in a single
1589 * flatten array using a packed format. The python part then unpacks the flatten array.
1590 *
1591 * The packed format for n records is:
1592 * {
1593 * int n;
1594 * int sizes[n+2]; // The sizes for the following arrays
1595 *
1596 * float features_0[size[0]]; // The features for record 0
1597 * float features_1[size[1]]; // The features for record 1
1598 * ...
1599 * float features_i[size[i]]; // The features for record i
1600 * ... // until i == n - 1
1601 *
1602 * float throughputs[sizes[n]]; // The normalized throughputs for n records
1603 * int task_ids[size[n+1]]; // The task ids for n records
1604 *
1605 * }
1606 * To implement this format, we also store int as float, so we can store all numbers
1607 * into a single float array.
1608 */
1609TVMByteArray SerializeFeatures(std::vector<std::vector<float>>&& features,
1610 std::vector<float>&& normalized_throughputs,
1611 std::vector<int>&& task_ids, std::vector<char>* out_data) {
1612 size_t total_bytes = 0;
1613 std::vector<int> size_vector;
1614
1615 int n = features.size();
1616
1617 // serialize sizes
1618 size_t size_vector_size = 1 + n + 2;
1619 total_bytes += size_vector_size * sizeof(int);
1620
1621 size_vector.reserve(size_vector_size);
1622 size_vector.push_back(features.size());
1623 for (const auto& x : features) {
1624 size_vector.push_back(static_cast<int>(x.size()));
1625 total_bytes += sizeof(float) * x.size();
1626 }
1627 size_vector.push_back(static_cast<int>(normalized_throughputs.size()));
1628 total_bytes += sizeof(float) * normalized_throughputs.size();
1629 size_vector.push_back(static_cast<int>(task_ids.size()));
1630 total_bytes += sizeof(int) * task_ids.size();
1631
1632 ICHECK_EQ(size_vector.size(), size_vector_size);
1633
1634 // allocate memory
1635 out_data->reserve(total_bytes);
1636 char* ptr = out_data->data();
1637
1638 // serialize size_vector
1639 memmove(ptr, reinterpret_cast<char*>(size_vector.data()), size_vector.size() * sizeof(int));
1640 ptr += size_vector.size() * sizeof(int);
1641
1642 // serialize features
1643 for (auto& x : features) {
1644 memmove(ptr, x.data(), sizeof(float) * x.size());
1645 ptr += sizeof(float) * x.size();
1646 x.clear();
1647 }
1648
1649 // serialize normalized_throughputs
1650 memmove(ptr, reinterpret_cast<char*>(normalized_throughputs.data()),
1651 normalized_throughputs.size() * sizeof(int));
1652 ptr += normalized_throughputs.size() * sizeof(int);
1653
1654 // serialize task_ids
1655 memmove(ptr, reinterpret_cast<char*>(task_ids.data()), task_ids.size() * sizeof(int));
1656 ptr += task_ids.size() * sizeof(int);
1657
1658 ICHECK_EQ(ptr - out_data->data(), total_bytes);
1659
1660 return TVMByteArray{out_data->data(), total_bytes};
1661}
1662
1663TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("auto_scheduler.GetPerStoreFeaturesFromFile")
1664 .set_body([](TVMArgs args, TVMRetValue* ret) {
1665 std::string filename = args[0];
1666 int max_lines = args[1];
1667 int max_n_bufs = args[2];
1668
1669 std::vector<std::vector<float>> features;
1670 std::vector<float> normalized_throughputs;
1671 std::vector<int> task_ids;
1672
1673 GetPerStoreFeaturesFromFile(filename, max_lines, max_n_bufs, &features,
1674 &normalized_throughputs, &task_ids);
1675

1732TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("auto_scheduler.FeaturesFromPrimFunc")
1733 .set_body_typed([](const PrimFunc& func, int cache_line_size, int max_n_bufs, bool log_scale) {
1734 std::vector<float> vec;
1735 GetPerStoreFeature(func, cache_line_size, max_n_bufs, &vec, log_scale);
1736 int64_t num_feature_rows = vec[0]; // first element is number of rows
1737 int64_t row_length = (vec.size() - 1) / num_feature_rows;
1738 auto ary =
1739 runtime::NDArray::Empty({num_feature_rows, row_length}, {kDLFloat, 32, 1}, {kDLCPU, 0});
1740 // NDArray is row major by default
1741 ary.CopyFromBytes(vec.data() + 1, sizeof(float) * num_feature_rows * row_length);
1742 return ary;
1743 });
